This manifest ships with default configuration files shipped with Debian
GNU/Linux 4.0 (etch). Ofcourse you _want_ to override the defaults. This can
be achieved by inheriting the manifest, e.g. like this:

# Override default PowerDNS configuration files.

class override-powerdns::master inherits powerdns::master {
	File["/etc/powerdns/pdns.conf"] {
		source => "puppet://puppet/override-powerdns/master-pdns.conf",
	}

	File["/etc/powerdns/pdns.d/pdns.local"] {
		source => "puppet://puppet/override-powerdns/master-pdns.local",
	}
}

class override-powerdns::slave inherits powerdns::slave {
	File["/etc/powerdns/pdns.conf"] {
		source => "puppet://puppet/override-powerdns/slave-pdns.conf",
	}

	File["/etc/powerdns/pdns.d/pdns.local"] {
		source => "puppet://puppet/override-powerdns/slave-pdns.local",
	}
}

In your own manifests, just "include override-powerdns::slave" will do.

	-Kees Meijs <kees@kumina.nl>, 11 February 2009
